The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Attack on AG
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Attack on AG
                            
	Imphal, March 6: The advocate-general of Manipur, N. Koteshore, was grievously injured after he was shot at by suspected militants in an ambush at Yaingangpokpi in Imphal East around 7.30pm on Saturday.        
	Koteshore was returning from Hungphung in Ukhrul district in a car when the attack took place. PWD minister K. Ranjit and tribal development minister D.D. Thaisii were accompanying him.        
	The 50-year-old Koteshore is undergoing treatment in hospital. His condition is stated to be serious.                                                                                                                                                          
